# Day 4 - Flow Builder

## 1. What is Flow Builder?

Flow Builder is a Salesforce automation tool used to automate business processes without writing code. It helps users create workflows using a visual drag-and-drop interface.

With Flow Builder, organizations can:
- Automate repetitive tasks
- Update records automatically
- Collect user input through screens
- Send notifications and emails
- Improve efficiency and reduce manual work

Flow Builder is one of the most powerful automation tools in Salesforce.

---

# 2. Types of Flows

## Screen Flow

A Screen Flow is a flow that interacts with users through screens. It collects information from users and performs actions based on the input.

### Features:
- User-friendly interface
- Collects data from users
- Can display messages and forms
- Used in apps, portals, and service systems

### Example:
A student registration form where users enter:
- Name
- Email
- Course
- Phone Number

The flow saves the information automatically.

---

## Record-Triggered Flow

A Record-Triggered Flow runs automatically when a record is:
- Created
- Updated
- Deleted

It helps automate backend processes without user interaction.

### Features:
- Fully automatic
- Runs in real time
- Reduces manual tasks
- Improves data consistency

### Example:
When an Opportunity status changes to "Closed Won":
- Send a confirmation email
- Create a follow-up task
- Update customer status automatically

